panCommonMibModule.name: panCommonMibModule

revisions.description: Rev 2.3 Added entries for Log Collector.
Rev 2.2 Added entries for Wildfire content versions. Added entry for new platform PA 3060.
Rev 2.1 Fixed a capitalization error with PanVsysEntry.
Rev 2.0 Updated with panGlobalProtect and panVsysTable.
Rev 1.0 Initial version of MIB module PAN-COMMON-MIB.

panCommonMibModule.contactinfo: Customer Support Palo Alto Networks 4401 Great America Pkwy Santa Clara, CA 95054-1211 +1 866-898-9087 support at paloaltonetworks dot com
panCommonMibModule.description: A MIB module containing definitions of managed objects implemented by all Palo Alto Networks' products.

panMgmt.name: panMgmt
panMgmt.description: Sub-tree for common Management plane information.

panLogCollector.name: panLogCollector
panLogCollector.description: Sub-tree for common Log Collector information.

panSysSwVersion.name: panSysSwVersion
panSysSwVersion.description: Full software version. The first two components of the full version are the major and minor versions. The third component indicates the maintenance release number and the fourth, the build number.

panSysSerialNumber.name: panSysSerialNumber
panSysSerialNumber.description: The serial number of the unit. If not available, an empty string is returned.

panSysTimeZoneOffset.name: panSysTimeZoneOffset
panSysTimeZoneOffset.description: The offset in seconds from UTC of the system's time zone. Values are negative for locations west of UTC and positive for locations east of UTC.

panSysDaylightSaving.name: panSysDaylightSaving
panSysDaylightSaving.description: Whether daylight savings are in currently in effect for the system's time zone.

panSysVpnClientVersion.name: panSysVpnClientVersion
panSysVpnClientVersion.description: Currently installed VPN client package version. If package is not installed, 0.0.0 is returned.

panSysAppVersion.name: panSysAppVersion
panSysAppVersion.description: Currently installed application definition version. If no application definition is found, 0 is returned.

panSysAvVersion.name: panSysAvVersion
panSysAvVersion.description: Currently installed antivirus version. If no antivirus is found, 0 is returned.

panSysThreatVersion.name: panSysThreatVersion
panSysThreatVersion.description: Currently installed threat definition version. If no threat definition is found, 0 is returned.

panSysUrlFilteringVersion.name: panSysUrlFilteringVersion
panSysUrlFilteringVersion.description: Currently installed URL filtering version. If no URL filtering is installed, 0 is returned.

panSysHAMode.name: panSysHAMode
panSysHAMode.description: Current high-availability mode (disabled, active-passive, or active-active).

panSysUrlFilteringDatabase.name: panSysUrlFilteringDatabase
panSysUrlFilteringDatabase.description: Current installed URL filtering database (surfcontrol, brightcloud, etc)

panSysGlobalProtectClientVersion.name: panSysGlobalProtectClientVersion
panSysGlobalProtectClientVersion.description: Currently installed global-protect client package version. If package is not installed, 0.0.0 is returned.

panSysOpswatDatafileVersion.name: panSysOpswatDatafileVersion
panSysOpswatDatafileVersion.description: Currently installed opswat database version. If package is not installed, 0 is returned.

panSysWildfireVersion.name: panSysWildfireVersion
panSysWildfireVersion.description: Currently installed wildfire content version. If no wildfire content is found, 0 is returned.

panSysWildfirePrivateCloudVersion.name: panSysWildfirePrivateCloudVersion
panSysWildfirePrivateCloudVersion.description: Currently installed wildfire private cloud content version. If no wpc is found, 0 is returned.

panChassisType.name: panChassisType
panChassisType.description: Chassis type for this Palo Alto device.

panMSeriesMode.name: panMSeriesMode
panMSeriesMode.description: Series Mode for this Palo Alto device.

panSessionUtilization.name: panSessionUtilization
panSessionUtilization.description: Session table utilization percentage. Values should be between 0 and 100.

panVsysEntry.description: Entries are created when the Vsys's are added to the entVsysTable.

panVsysName.name: panVsysName
panVsysName.description: User assigned vsys name (empty string if not available)

panVsysSessionUtilizationPct.name: panVsysSessionUtilizationPct
panVsysSessionUtilizationPct.description: Vsys utilization percentage, if session limit is configured. If session limit is not configured, this value is '0'

panVsysMaxSessions.description: Max sessions on this Vsys, if session limit is configured. If session limit is not configured, this value is '0'
